Johnny Edward The Nigerian Basketball Federation have named Mike Brown as the new D’Tigers coach ahead of the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, Sports Extra reports. Brown, who is the Golden State Warriors assistant coach, will be assisted by Alex Nwora who guided the team to qualification for the Olympics. A top source revealed to The Punch that Brown’s appointment will help the NBBF immensely in terms of player recruitment in the MAN. Miami Heats’ Bam Adebayo and Indiana Pavers Victor Oladipo have both been courted by the NBBF “Mike Brown has been named the head coach of the D’Tigers for the 2020 Olympics.Welcome aboard Coach Brown,” a tweet from the D’Tigers Twitter handle revealed. Meanwhile Shane Lawal has announced that he has come out of retirement following the NBBF’s appointment of Brown. Lawal called it quits from D’Tigers “I’d like to announce my unretirement from Basketball.” Lawal tweeted. In 2012, Nigeria became the only African nation to ever qualify for the Summer Olympics through the FIBA World Olympic Qualifying Tournament. In 2015, Nigeria won its first basketball championship of Africa. Copyright PUNCH.
